SYNOPSIS
	void add_attribute( string attr)
	void add_attribute( string attr, int value)
	void add_attribute( string attr, object obj)
	void add_attribute( string attr, int value, object obj)

DESCRIPTION
	Add a deletable attribute with the name 'attr' to an object.
	If no object 'obj' is given, the current object is used.
	If no 'value' is given, 1 is used.

SEE ALSO
	attributes(C), add_prot_attribute(E), delete_attribute(E),
	get_attribute(E), query_attribute(E)
